   [concat] ==============================================

     [java]                  Geometry primitives include the 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Box" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Box&lt;/a&gt;,

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Sphere" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Sphere&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Text" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Text&lt;/a&gt; nodes.
     [java]                  Each is placed individually inside a
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;

     [java]                 &lt;td&gt;
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                     Grouping nodes help to organize the scene graph, can establish relative coordinate systems,
     [java]                     and can contain most other kinds of X3D nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Grouping nodes include the 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Anchor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Anchor&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Billboard" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Billboard&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Collision" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Collision&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Group" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Group&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#StaticGroup" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;StaticGroup&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Switch" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Switch&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Transform" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Transform&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]                  The 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Inline" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Inline&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node is also similar since it adds nodes into the current scene that loaded from another X3D scene, retrieved
     [java]                  via a local or online url address.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting

     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#3" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via

     [java]                 &lt;td align="left" rowspan="2"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="Anchor comparison, view from front" title="Anchor comparison, view from front" border="0" hspace="10" src="AnchorComparisonFrontViewpoint.png" width="87" height="101" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                 
     [java]                 &lt;td align="left"&gt;
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Viewpoint" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Viewpoint&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                     nodes are the primary means for users to explore a scene.
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NavigationInfo" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NavigationInfo&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                     nodes enable different user-interaction styles (FLY, WALK, EXAMINE etc.) as appropriate.
     [java]                     Only one Viewpoint and one NavigationInfo node can each be active a time,
     [java]                     with order of selection controlled via a binding stack.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java]

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ImageTexture" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ImageTexture&lt;/a&gt;,

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Event animation and interpolation is accomplished by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ROUTE" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ROUTE&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  connections that pass events between nodes.
     [java]                  Strong typing requirements ensure that only valid values are allowed to modify the scene graph.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TimeSensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TimeSensor&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node produces output stimulus events that track the passage of time intervals using the computer clock.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PositionInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PositionInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PositionInterpolator2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PositionInterpolator2D&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#OrientationInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;OrientationInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NormalInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NormalInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,

     [java]                  User interactivity is accomplished by sensing user actions, which create events that are sent via 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ROUTE" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ROUTE&lt;/a&gt;

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Polypoint2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Polypoint2D&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Rectangle2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Rectangle2D&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  and

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Lights illuminate geometry in a scene relative to the user's view.
     [java]                  Lighting nodes include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#DirectionalLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;DirectionalLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PointLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PointLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#SpotLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;SpotLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and the active 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NavigationInfo" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NavigationInfo&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  headlight (which points along the user's viewing direction).
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;                 
     [java]                  Environmental effects include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Background" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Background&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureBackground" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureBackground&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Fog" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Fog&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LocalFog" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LocalFog&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                  Each set of light nodes, NavigationInfo nodes, background nodes and fog nodes are bound on a separate binding stack,
     [java]                  meaning that only one of each can be active at a time.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Low-level high-performance nodes for geometry definition and fast rendering include
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TriangleSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TriangleSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TriangleFanSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TriangleFanSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TriangleStripSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TriangleStripSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedTriangleSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedTriangleSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedTriangleFanSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedTriangleFanSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedTriangleStripSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedTriangleStripSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#QuadSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;QuadSet&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedQuadSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedQuadSet&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                 Special definition rules apply to each node in order to best match underlying graphics hardware requirements.
     [java]                  Each is placed individually inside a
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node.

     [java]                  and

     [java] X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes package.html $packagePath=../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes/package.html, $packageBodyFragment=fn:doc(../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes/package.html)=

     [java]     &lt;table bgColor="#ffffff" border="0" width="100%"&gt;

     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img title="ViewFrustum prototype demonstration" alt="ViewFrustum prototype demonstration" border="0" hspace="0" src="ViewFrustumObliqueView.png" width="253" height="112" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  X3D extensibility includes a tremendous capability: 
     [java]                  authors can create prototype declarations and instances to define new X3D nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Prototype templates are built using 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoDeclare" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoDeclare&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  or 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ExternProtoDeclare" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ExternProtoDeclare&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  definitions.
     [java]                  
     [java]                  ProtoDeclare field definitions are found in the
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoInterface" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoInterface&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  tag, which can include multiple
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#field" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declarations that define a name, initial value (if appropriate),
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#accessType" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;accessType&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (inputOnly, outputOnly, initializeOnly and inputOutput)
     [java]                  and  
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#type" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;type&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  for each field.
     [java]                  The type of each node is defined by the first node inside the 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoBody" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoBody&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declaration.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Copies of a new node are created by name with 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoInstance" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoInstance&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]                  Default values for ProtoInstance fields can be overridden with
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#fieldValue" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;fieldValue&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  initializations.
     [java]                  A ProtoInstance node can replace any other node in the scene graph having the same node type.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;14 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#14" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                      Also available:
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      for
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#InlinesPrototypes" target="_blank"&gt;Inline Scenes and Prototype Templates&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                       and
     [java]                       &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#urls" target="_blank"&gt;URL&amp;nbsp;Links&lt;/a&gt;.

     [java] X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter15-Metadata package.html $packagePath=../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter15-Metadata/package.html, $packageBodyFragment=fn:doc(../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter15-Metadata/package.html)=
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;table border="0" width="100%"&gt;
     [java]         &lt;tbody&gt;
     [java]             &lt;tr&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td align="center" rowspan="2"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img border="0" alt="Metadata (book with question mark)" title="Metadata (book with question mark)" hspace="10" src="200px-Question_book-new.svg.png" width="100" height="78" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td align="left"&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metadata" target="_blank"&gt;Metadata&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  is about forms of data relating to other data.
     [java]                  For example, metadata can provide a variety of information regarding a document such as author, date revised, relevant key words, etc.
     [java]                  As another example, metadata might annotate X3D CAD geometry to provide key references such as part numbers, documentation references, inventory links, etc.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Simple name=value paired information can be provided in document
     [java]                  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#head" target="X3dTooltips"&gt;head&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#meta" target="X3dTooltips"&gt;meta&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
     [java]                  tags, just like in HTML.
     [java]                  Furthermore, typed metadata information can annotate any X3D node, either for use offline or for queries within an active scene graph at run time.
     [java]                  X3D metadata nodes include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataBoolean" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataBoolean&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataDouble" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataDouble&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataFloat" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataFloat&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataInteger" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataInteger&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataString" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataString&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataSet&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (which contains a collection of other X3D Metadata nodes).
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="Chapter15-MetadataInformation.html" target="_blank"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;15 Metadata Information&lt;/a&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; is
     [java]                  available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com/"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                  
     [java]                 Also available:
     [java] 
     [java]                 &lt;ul&gt;
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#metaTags" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints: meta Tags&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/Savage/Tools/SMAL/SMAL.html" target="_blank"&gt;Savage Modeling and Analysis Language (SMAL) Resources&lt;/a&gt; reference website,
     [java]                        plus
     [java]                        &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/Savage/Tools/SMAL/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;Savage/Tools/SMAL&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                        example-archive template scenes showing matching X3D/XML metadata.
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        Rauch, Travis M.,
     [java]                        &lt;a href="http://calhoun.nps.edu/public/handle/10945/2971" target="_blank"&gt;Savage Modeling and Analysis Language (SMAL) metadata for tactical simulations and X3D visualizations&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                        Masters Thesis, Naval Postgraduate School, Monterey, California, 2006.
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/ul&gt;

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                 The 
     [java]                 &lt;a href="KelpForestMain.x3d" target="kelpScene"&gt;Kelp Forest Exhibit&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 is a large
     [java]                 &lt;a href="http://faculty.nps.edu/brutzman/kelp" target="kelpPaper"&gt;student-produced project&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 that illustrates how X3D can build and integrate a large collection of individual Web-based models.
     [java]                 The overall scene that integrates all these individual X3D models is
     [java]                 &lt;a href="KelpForestMain.x3d" target="kelpScene"&gt;Kelp Forest Main&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                 The paper
     [java]                 &lt;a href="http://faculty.nps.edu/brutzman/kelp/KelpForestDesignPaper.pdf" target="kelpPaper"&gt;Teaching 3D Modeling and Simulation: Virtual Kelp Forest Case Study&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 describes how this group effort was accomplished.
     [java]                 Comprehensive modeling efforts such as the Kelp Forest Exhibit provide an excellent way to organize course work and student projects.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java]

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                      Introductory slidesets for
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter00-GettingStarted.pdf"&gt;Getting Started&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      and
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter00-GettingStarted.pdf"&gt;X3D-Edit Update&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      describe good ways to begin learning and authoring X3D.
     [java]                      The supporting
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets"&gt;slidesets&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                      &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      and the complete
     [java]                      &lt;a href="Chapter01-Technical_Overview.pdf"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;1 Technical Overview&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]                  All of these examples were created using the
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/X3D-Edit"&gt;X3D-Edit authoring tool&lt;/a&gt;.  
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  
     [java]                  A published paper
     [java]                  "&lt;a href="CGEMS_X3dGraphicsForWebAuthorsModule_Brutzman2008October16.pdf"&gt;Computer Graphics Teaching Support using X3D&lt;/a&gt;"
     [java]                  describes how X3D is used to teach introductory 3D in university courses.
     [java]                  Together these assets can be used to learn X3D.   
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Shape nodes can contain one geometry node and one Appearance node.
     [java]                  Geometry primitives include the 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Box" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Box&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Cone" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Cone&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Cylinder" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Cylinder&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Sphere" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Sphere&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Text" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Text&lt;/a&gt; nodes.
     [java]                  Each is placed individually inside a
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java]

     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="Coordinate Axes (North South East West)" title="Coordinate Axes (North South East West)" border="0" hspace="10" src="CoordinateAxesNSEW.WhiteBackground.png" width="163" height="177" align="left"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                 &lt;td&gt;
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                     Grouping nodes help to organize the scene graph, can establish relative coordinate systems,
     [java]                     and can contain most other kinds of X3D nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Grouping nodes include the 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Anchor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Anchor&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Billboard" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Billboard&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Collision" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Collision&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Group" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Group&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#StaticGroup" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;StaticGroup&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Switch" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Switch&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Transform" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Transform&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]                  The 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Inline" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Inline&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node is also similar since it adds nodes into the current scene that loaded from another X3D scene, retrieved
     [java]                  via a local or online url address.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter03-Grouping.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;3 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#3" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Also available:
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  for
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#CoordinateSystems" target="_blank"&gt;Coordinate Systems&lt;/a&gt;,

     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="Anchor comparison, view from front" title="Anchor comparison, view from front" border="0" hspace="10" src="AnchorComparisonFrontViewpoint.png" width="87" height="101" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

     [java]

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Viewpoint" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Viewpoint&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                     nodes are the primary means for users to explore a scene.
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NavigationInfo" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NavigationInfo&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                     nodes enable different user-interaction styles (FLY, WALK, EXAMINE etc.) as appropriate.
     [java]                     Only one Viewpoint and one NavigationInfo node can each be active a time,
     [java]                     with order of selection controlled via a binding stack.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;

     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter04-ViewingNavigation.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;4 slideset&lt;/a&gt;

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Appearance" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Appearance&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  is individually associated with specific geometry within a shared 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node.
     [java]                  
     [java]                  Each Appearance is a container node that can include 
     [java]                  
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Material" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Material&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TwoSidedMaterial" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TwoSidedMaterial&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ImageTexture" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ImageTexture&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MovieTexture" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MovieTexture&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PixelTexture" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PixelTexture&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MultiTexture" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MultiTexture&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Appearance can also contain property nodes for controlling rendering and texture:
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#FillProperties" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;FillProperties&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LineProperties" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LineProperties&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureProperties" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureProperties&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureTransform" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureTransform&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MultiTextureTransform" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MultiTextureTransform&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Many kinds of geometry can be created using 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PointSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PointSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LineSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LineSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedLineSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedLineSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedFaceSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedFaceSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ElevationGrid" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ElevationGrid&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Extrusion" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Extrusion&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]                  Each is placed individually inside a
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Geometric properties are controlled by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Color" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Color&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ColorRGBA" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ColorRGBA&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Coordinate" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Coordinate&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#CoordinateDouble" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;CoordinateDouble&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Normal" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Normal&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureCoordinate" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureCoordinate&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureCoordinateGenerator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureCoordinateGenerator&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MultiTextureCoordinate" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MultiTextureCoordinate&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java]

     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="Color Per Vertex Examples" title="Color Per Vertex Examples" border="0" hspace="0" src="ColorPerVertexExamples.png" width="600" height="100" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]             &lt;/tr&gt;

     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Many kinds of geometry can be created using 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PointSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PointSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LineSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LineSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedLineSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedLineSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedFaceSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedFaceSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ElevationGrid" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ElevationGrid&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Extrusion" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Extrusion&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]                  Each is placed individually inside a
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Geometric properties are controlled by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Color" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Color&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ColorRGBA" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ColorRGBA&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Coordinate" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Coordinate&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#CoordinateDouble" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;CoordinateDouble&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Normal" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Normal&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureCoordinate" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureCoordinate&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureCoordinateGenerator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureCoordinateGenerator&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MultiTextureCoordinate" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MultiTextureCoordinate&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;

     [java]     &lt;table bgColor="#ffffff" border="0" width="100%"&gt;
     [java]         &lt;tbody&gt;
     [java]             &lt;tr&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td width="100%" align="center"&gt;
     [java]                     &lt;br /&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="Dolphin Wireframe: Coordinate Interpolator Morphing" title="Dolphin Wireframe: Coordinate Interpolator Morphing" border="0" hspace="0" src="DolphinWireframe.png" width="350" height="105" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]             &lt;/tr&gt;
     [java]         &lt;/tbody&gt;
     [java]     &lt;/table&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Event animation and interpolation is accomplished by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ROUTE" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ROUTE&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  connections that pass events between nodes.
     [java]                  Strong typing requirements ensure that only valid values are allowed to modify the scene graph.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TimeSensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TimeSensor&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node produces output stimulus events that track the passage of time intervals using the computer clock.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Strictly typed interpolation values are produced by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ScalarInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ScalarInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ColorInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ColorInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PositionInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PositionInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PositionInterpolator2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PositionInterpolator2D&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#OrientationInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;OrientationInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NormalInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NormalInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;, 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#CoordinateInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;CoordinateInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#CoordinateInterpolator2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;CoordinateInterpolator2D&lt;/a&gt; nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter07-EventAnimationInterpolation.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;7 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#7" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;

     [java]                     &lt;br /&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="Dolphin Wireframe: Coordinate Interpolator Morphing" title="Dolphin Wireframe: Coordinate Interpolator Morphing" border="0" hspace="0" src="DolphinWireframe.png" width="350" height="105" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]             &lt;/tr&gt;
     [java]         &lt;/tbody&gt;
     [java]     &lt;/table&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Event animation and interpolation is accomplished by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ROUTE" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ROUTE&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  connections that pass events between nodes.
     [java]                  Strong typing requirements ensure that only valid values are allowed to modify the scene graph.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TimeSensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TimeSensor&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node produces output stimulus events that track the passage of time intervals using the computer clock.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Strictly typed interpolation values are produced by 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ScalarInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ScalarInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ColorInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ColorInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PositionInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PositionInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PositionInterpolator2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PositionInterpolator2D&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#OrientationInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;OrientationInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NormalInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NormalInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;, 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#CoordinateInterpolator" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;CoordinateInterpolator&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#CoordinateInterpolator2D" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;CoordinateInterpolator2D&lt;/a&gt; nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter07-EventAnimationInterpolation.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;7 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#7" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#KeySensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;KeySensor&lt;/a&gt;

     [java] X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter09-EventUtilitiesScripting package.html $packagePath=../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter09-EventUtilitiesScripting/package.html, $packageBodyFragment=fn:doc(../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter09-EventUtilitiesScripting/package.html)=

     [java]     &lt;table bgColor="#ffffff" border="0" width="100%"&gt;
     [java]         &lt;tbody&gt;
     [java]             &lt;tr&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td align="left" cellpadding="10"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="IntegerSequencer example:  Road Work Ahead!" title="IntegerSequencer example:  Road Work Ahead!" border="0" hspace="10" src="RoadSignRoadWorkAhead.jpg" width="205" height="153" align="left"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                 &lt;td&gt;
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Event utility nodes simplify data-type conversion of events when producing animation chains between nodes.
     [java]                  These include
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#BooleanFilter" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;BooleanFilter&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#BooleanSequencer" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;BooleanSequencer&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#BooleanToggle" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;BooleanToggle&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IntegerSequencer" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IntegerSequencer&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IntegerTrigger" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IntegerTrigger&lt;/a&gt;, 
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TimeTrigger" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TimeTrigger&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The quick-reference sheet
     [java]                  &lt;a href="X3dEventUtilityNodeEventDiagrams.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;X3D&amp;nbsp;Event&amp;nbsp;Utility&amp;nbsp;Nodes: Field&amp;nbsp;Event&amp;nbsp;Diagrams&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  illustrates the functionality of the event utility nodes.
     [java]                  These nodes receive and pass values that are sent via 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ROUTE" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ROUTE&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  connections.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Script" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Script&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node allows authors to define new functionality produced by JavaScript (ECMAscript) or Java code.
     [java]                  Authors can add
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#field" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declarations that define 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#accessType" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;accessType&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (inputOnly, outputOnly, initializeOnly and inputOutput)
     [java]                  and  
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#type" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;type&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  for each field.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter09-EventUtilitiesScripting.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;9 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#9" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;

     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#Images" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      for
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#Scripts" target="_blank"&gt;Scripts&lt;/a&gt;

     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img alt="DirectionalLight Diagram" title="DirectionalLight Diagram" border="0" hspace="10" src="DirectionalLightFigure.png" width="303" height="156" align="left"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

     [java] 
     [java]                 &lt;td&gt;               
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Lights illuminate geometry in a scene relative to the user's view.
     [java]                  Lighting nodes include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#DirectionalLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;DirectionalLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PointLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PointLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#SpotLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;SpotLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and the active 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NavigationInfo" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NavigationInfo&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  headlight (which points along the user's viewing direction).
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;                 
     [java]                  Environmental effects include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Background" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Background&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureBackground" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureBackground&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Fog" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Fog&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LocalFog" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LocalFog&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                  Each set of light nodes, NavigationInfo nodes, background nodes and fog nodes are bound on a separate binding stack,
     [java]                  meaning that only one of each can be active at a time.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter11-LightingEnvironment.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;11 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#11" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#DirectionalLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;DirectionalLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#PointLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;PointLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#SpotLight" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;SpotLight&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and the active 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#NavigationInfo" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;NavigationInfo&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  headlight (which points along the user's viewing direction).
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;                 
     [java]                  Environmental effects include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Background" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Background&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#TextureBackground" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;TextureBackground&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Fog" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Fog&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LocalFog" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LocalFog&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                  Each set of light nodes, NavigationInfo nodes, background nodes and fog nodes are bound on a separate binding stack,
     [java]                  meaning that only one of each can be active at a time.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter11-LightingEnvironment.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;11 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#11" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]             &lt;/tr&gt;

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                      Event-producing environmental sensor nodes include
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#LoadSensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;LoadSensor&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProximitySensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProximitySensor&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                      and 
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#VisibilitySensor" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;VisibilitySensor&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                      Audio nodes include 
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Sound" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Sound&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      for aural spatialization and 
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#AudioClip" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;AudioClip&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      for identifying sound files.
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MovieTexture" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MovieTexture&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      nodes can also be used as an audio soundtrack source.    &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                     Relevant
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/files/specifications/19775-1/V3.3/Part01/Architecture.html" target="X3dSpecification"&gt;X3D Specification&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                     resources include the
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/files/specifications/19775-1/V3.3/Part01/components/envsensor.html" target="X3dSpecification"&gt;Environmental sensor component&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/files/specifications/19775-1/V3.3/Part01/components/sound.html" target="X3dSpecification"&gt;Sound component&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                     and
     [java]                     &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/files/specifications/19775-1/V3.3/Part01/components/texturing.html" target="X3dSpecification"&gt;Texturing component&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedTriangleStripSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedTriangleStripSet&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#QuadSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;QuadSet&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#IndexedQuadSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;IndexedQuadSet&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                 Special definition rules apply to each node in order to best match underlying graphics hardware requirements.
     [java]                  Each is placed individually inside a
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#Shape" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;Shape&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  node.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter13-GeometryTrianglesQuadrilaterals.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;13 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#13" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;

     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.

     [java]                  X3D extensibility includes a tremendous capability: 
     [java]                  authors can create prototype declarations and instances to define new X3D nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Prototype templates are built using 
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[17] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Kelp Forest Monterey Bay Aquarium' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Kelp_Forest_Monterey_Bay_Aquarium.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoDeclare" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoDeclare&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  or 
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[18] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Side Windows' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Side_Windows.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ExternProtoDeclare" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ExternProtoDeclare&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  definitions.
     [java]                  
     [java]                  ProtoDeclare field definitions are found in the
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[19] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Star Fish' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Star_Fish.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoInterface" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoInterface&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  tag, which can include multiple
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#field" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declarations that define a name, initial value (if appropriate),
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[20] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Inside Tank' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Inside_Tank.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#accessType" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;accessType&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (inputOnly, outputOnly, initializeOnly and inputOutput)
     [java]                  and  
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[21] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Top floor' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Top_floor.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#type" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;type&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  for each field.
     [java]                  The type of each node is defined by the first node inside the 
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[22] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Bird&amp;amp;apos;s Eye View' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Bird&amp;amp;apos;s_Eye_View.png' found='false'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoBody" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoBody&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declaration.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[23] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - Pump House' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Pump_House.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  Copies of a new node are created by name with 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoInstance" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoInstance&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[24] LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d - (default X3D view from 0 0 10)' fileName='LoadSensor-KelpForestMain_timeOut.x3d._VP_Default_viewpoint.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  Default values for ProtoInstance fields can be overridden with
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#fieldValue" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;fieldValue&lt;/a&gt;
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[25] LoadSensor.x3d - LoadSensor test' fileName='LoadSensor.x3d._VP_LoadSensor_test.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  initializations.
     [java]                  A ProtoInstance node can replace any other node in the scene graph having the same node type.
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[26] LoadSensor.x3d - (default X3D view from 0 0 10)' fileName='LoadSensor.x3d._VP_Default_viewpoint.png' found='true'/>
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;14 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[27] ProximitySensor-KelpForestMain.x3d - Kelp Forest Monterey Bay Aquarium' fileName='ProximitySensor-KelpForestMain.x3d._VP_Kelp_Forest_Monterey_Bay_Aquarium.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#14" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[28] ProximitySensor-KelpForestMain.x3d - Side Windows' fileName='ProximitySensor-KelpForestMain.x3d._VP_Side_Windows.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.

     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      for
     [java] <Viewpoint description='[30] ProximitySensor-KelpForestMain.x3d - Inside Tank' fileName='ProximitySensor-KelpForestMain.x3d._VP_Inside_Tank.png' found='true'/>
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#InlinesPrototypes" target="_blank"&gt;Inline Scenes and Prototype Templates&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                       and
     [java]                       &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#urls" target="_blank"&gt;URL&amp;nbsp;Links&lt;/a&gt;.

     [java] X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes package.html $packagePath=../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes/package.html, $packageBodyFragment=fn:doc(../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes/package.html)=

     [java]     &lt;table bgColor="#ffffff" border="0" width="100%"&gt;
     [java]         &lt;tbody&gt;

     [java]                 &lt;td align="right"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img title="MaterialModulator prototype demonstration" alt="MaterialModulator prototype demonstration" border="0" hspace="0" src="MaterialModulator.png" height="112" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                 
     [java]                 &lt;td  align="left"&gt;
     [java]                     &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                 
     [java]                 &lt;td  align="left"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img title="ViewFrustum prototype demonstration" alt="ViewFrustum prototype demonstration" border="0" hspace="0" src="ViewFrustumObliqueView.png" width="253" height="112" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]             &lt;/tr&gt;
     [java]         &lt;/tbody&gt;
     [java]     &lt;/table&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  X3D extensibility includes a tremendous capability: 
     [java]                  authors can create prototype declarations and instances to define new X3D nodes.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Prototype templates are built using 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoDeclare" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoDeclare&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  or 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ExternProtoDeclare" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ExternProtoDeclare&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  definitions.
     [java]                  
     [java]                  ProtoDeclare field definitions are found in the
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoInterface" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoInterface&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  tag, which can include multiple
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#field" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declarations that define a name, initial value (if appropriate),
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#accessType" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;accessType&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (inputOnly, outputOnly, initializeOnly and inputOutput)
     [java]                  and  
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#type" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;type&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  for each field.
     [java]                  The type of each node is defined by the first node inside the 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoBody" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoBody&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  declaration.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Copies of a new node are created by name with 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#ProtoInstance" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;ProtoInstance&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  nodes.
     [java]                  Default values for ProtoInstance fields can be overridden with
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#fieldValue" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;fieldValue&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  initializations.
     [java]                  A ProtoInstance node can replace any other node in the scene graph having the same node type.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://x3dgraphics.com/slidesets/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter14-Prototypes.pdf" target="X3dChapterSlideset"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;14 slideset&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;a href="https://www.movesinstitute.org/Video/Courses/X3dForWebAuthors/X3dForWebAuthorsVideo.html#14" target="X3dChapterVideos"&gt;course videos&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; are available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                      Also available:
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                      for
     [java]                      &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#InlinesPrototypes" target="_blank"&gt;Inline Scenes and Prototype Templates&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                       and
     [java]                       &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#urls" target="_blank"&gt;URL&amp;nbsp;Links&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
