     [java] *** Chapter Chapter15-Metadata, next chapter found=KelpForestExhibit/index.html
     [java] X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter15-Metadata package.html $packagePath=../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter15-Metadata/package.html, $packageBodyFragment=fn:doc(../../content/examples/X3dForWebAuthors/Chapter15-Metadata/package.html)=
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;table border="0" width="100%"&gt;
     [java]         &lt;tbody&gt;
     [java]             &lt;tr&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td align="center" rowspan="2"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img border="0" alt="Metadata (book with question mark)" title="Metadata (book with question mark)" hspace="10" src="200px-Question_book-new.svg.png" width="100" height="78" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td align="left"&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metadata" target="_blank"&gt;Metadata&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  is about forms of data relating to other data.
     [java]                  For example, metadata can provide a variety of information regarding a document such as author, date revised, relevant key words, etc.
     [java]                  As another example, metadata might annotate X3D CAD geometry to provide key references such as part numbers, documentation references, inventory links, etc.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Simple name=value paired information can be provided in document
     [java]                  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#head" target="X3dTooltips"&gt;head&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#meta" target="X3dTooltips"&gt;meta&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
     [java]                  tags, just like in HTML.
     [java]                  Furthermore, typed metadata information can annotate any X3D node, either for use offline or for queries within an active scene graph at run time.
     [java]                  X3D metadata nodes include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataBoolean" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataBoolean&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataDouble" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataDouble&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataFloat" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataFloat&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataInteger" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataInteger&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataString" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataString&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataSet&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (which contains a collection of other X3D Metadata nodes).
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="Chapter15-MetadataInformation.html" target="_blank"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;15 Metadata Information&lt;/a&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; is
     [java]                  available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com/"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                  
     [java]                 Also available:
     [java] 
     [java]                 &lt;ul&gt;
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#metaTags" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints: meta Tags&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/Savage/Tools/SMAL/SMAL.html" target="_blank"&gt;Savage Modeling and Analysis Language (SMAL) Resources&lt;/a&gt; reference website,
     [java]                        plus
     [java]                        &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/Savage/Tools/SMAL/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;Savage/Tools/SMAL&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                        example-archive template scenes showing matching X3D/XML metadata.
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        Rauch, Travis M.,
     [java]                        &lt;a href="http://calhoun.nps.edu/public/handle/10945/2971" target="_blank"&gt;Savage Modeling and Analysis Language (SMAL) metadata for tactical simulations and X3D visualizations&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                        Masters Thesis, Naval Postgraduate School, Monterey, California, 2006.
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/ul&gt;
     [java]                      
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java]

     [java] 
     [java]

     [java]         &lt;tbody&gt;

     [java]                 &lt;td align="center" rowspan="2"&gt;
     [java]                     
     [java]                     &lt;a href="index.html"&gt;&lt;img border="0" alt="Metadata (book with question mark)" title="Metadata (book with question mark)" hspace="10" src="200px-Question_book-new.svg.png" width="100" height="78" align="middle"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/td&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;td align="left"&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metadata" target="_blank"&gt;Metadata&lt;/a&gt; 
     [java]                  is about forms of data relating to other data.
     [java]                  For example, metadata can provide a variety of information regarding a document such as author, date revised, relevant key words, etc.
     [java]                  As another example, metadata might annotate X3D CAD geometry to provide key references such as part numbers, documentation references, inventory links, etc.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  Simple name=value paired information can be provided in document
     [java]                  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#head" target="X3dTooltips"&gt;head&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
     [java]                  and
     [java]                  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#meta" target="X3dTooltips"&gt;meta&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;
     [java]                  tags, just like in HTML.
     [java]                  Furthermore, typed metadata information can annotate any X3D node, either for use offline or for queries within an active scene graph at run time.
     [java]                  X3D metadata nodes include 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataBoolean" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataBoolean&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataDouble" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataDouble&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataFloat" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataFloat&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataInteger" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataInteger&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataString" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataString&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                  and 
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/X3dTooltips.html#MetadataSet" target="X3dTooltips" title="X3D Tooltip"&gt;MetadataSet&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                  (which contains a collection of other X3D Metadata nodes).
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java] 
     [java] 
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                  The supporting
     [java]                  &lt;a href="Chapter15-MetadataInformation.html" target="_blank"&gt;Chapter&amp;nbsp;15 Metadata Information&lt;/a&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                  from &lt;i&gt;X3D for Web Authors&lt;/i&gt; is
     [java]                  available online via
     [java]                  &lt;a href="http://X3dGraphics.com/"&gt;X3dGraphics.com&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]                  
     [java]                 Also available:
     [java] 
     [java]                 &lt;ul&gt;
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        &lt;a href="http://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/X3dSceneAuthoringHints.html#metaTags" target="_blank"&gt;X3D Scene Authoring Hints: meta Tags&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/Savage/Tools/SMAL/SMAL.html" target="_blank"&gt;Savage Modeling and Analysis Language (SMAL) Resources&lt;/a&gt; reference website,
     [java]                        plus
     [java]                        &lt;a href="https://savage.nps.edu/Savage/Tools/SMAL/index.html" target="_blank"&gt;Savage/Tools/SMAL&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                        example-archive template scenes showing matching X3D/XML metadata.
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java] 
     [java]                    &lt;li&gt;
     [java]                        Rauch, Travis M.,
     [java]                        &lt;a href="http://calhoun.nps.edu/public/handle/10945/2971" target="_blank"&gt;Savage Modeling and Analysis Language (SMAL) metadata for tactical simulations and X3D visualizations&lt;/a&gt;,
     [java]                        Masters Thesis, Naval Postgraduate School, Monterey, California, 2006.
     [java]                    &lt;/li&gt;
     [java]                 &lt;/ul&gt;
     [java]                      
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     
     [java]

     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                 The 
     [java]                 &lt;a href="KelpForestMain.x3d" target="kelpScene"&gt;Kelp Forest Exhibit&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 is a large
     [java]                 &lt;a href="http://faculty.nps.edu/brutzman/kelp" target="kelpPaper"&gt;student-produced project&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 that illustrates how X3D can build and integrate a large collection of individual Web-based models.
     [java]                 The overall scene that integrates all these individual X3D models is
     [java]                 &lt;a href="KelpForestMain.x3d" target="kelpScene"&gt;Kelp Forest Main&lt;/a&gt;.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
     [java]     &lt;p&gt;
     [java]                 The paper
     [java]                 &lt;a href="http://faculty.nps.edu/brutzman/kelp/KelpForestDesignPaper.pdf" target="kelpPaper"&gt;Teaching 3D Modeling and Simulation: Virtual Kelp Forest Case Study&lt;/a&gt;
     [java]                 describes how this group effort was accomplished.
     [java]                 Comprehensive modeling efforts such as the Kelp Forest Exhibit provide an excellent way to organize course work and student projects.
     [java]     &lt;/p&gt;
